This place is super great. I absolutely love the fusion of sushi and burritos (two of my favorite things) into this positively amazing combination. The customer service is pretty great when you're in the actual store, but the service that we received when we catered from them for an event in February was fairly lackluster (our delivery was several hours late and they were almost impossible to contact). It is pretty expensive for the portion, but it's still reasonable, especially for D.C. I used to work in a sushi burrito restaurant and Buredo is definitely significantly better. Their rice is well seasoned, the nori is perfectly soft and has enough flavor on its own, and the fillings are all portioned perfectly to create a great balance of flavors and textures. I've only tried the Beatrix (yellowfin tuna and salmon sashimi with cucumber, pickled cabbage, green onion, tempura crunch, and unagi sauce) and Hanzo (yellowfin tuna with avocado, cucumber, pickled fennel, arugula, tempura crunch, and lemon aioli), and both were phenomenal.

Only one thing to note for others: they only have one vegan option, and one additional vegetarian option, so if you are one or the other, then your choices are pretty limited.
